'''Nyoshul Khenpo Rinpoche''' (1932-1999) was a [[Tibetan Buddhism|Tibetan]] [[lama]] born in the Derge region of Kham.<ref name="trib">[http://www.rangjung.com/authors/Nyoshul_Khen_Rinpoche_tribute.htm Tribute to Nyoshul Khenpo Jamyang Dorje]</ref><ref name="lineage">[http://www.dzogchen.org/library/bios/dzogchen-lineage.htm The Dzogchen Lineage of Nyoshul Khenpo]</ref>

At age five, Rinpoche joined a [[Sakya]] monastery where he began his [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] studies.<ref name="trib"/> At age seventeen, he studied [[Longchen Nyingthig]] teachings<ref name="trib"/> and [[Dzogchen]]<ref name="lineage"/> at the Nyoshul monastery.<ref name="trib"/> In 1959, when he was twenty seven, he fled to India as the [[Invasion of Tibet (1950)|Chinese invaded Tibet]].<ref name="bayarea">[http://www.rigpabayarea.org/nyoshul_khenpo.html Nyoshul Khen Rinpoche]</ref><ref name="trib"/>

In India, Rinpoche studied under [[Dudjom Rinpoche]],<ref name="bayarea"/> [[Dilgo Khyentse Rinpoche]]<ref name="bayarea"/> and the [[Rangjung Rigpe Dorje, 16th Karmapa Lama|16th Gyalwang Karmapa]].<ref name="trib"/>

Some of Rinpoche's students include [[Surya Das|Lama Surya Das]]<ref>[http://www.dzogchen.org/library/bios/nyoshulk.htm Nyoshul Khenpo Rinpoche]</ref><ref>[http://www.dzogchen.org/guests/NKR%20Blessing%20Tibetan.htm  Certificate of Dharma Transmission and Authorization to Lama Surya Das]</ref> and [[Sogyal Rinpoche]].<ref>[http://www.lotsawahouse.org/sogyal.html Lotsawa House: Sogyal Rinpoche]</ref>

